name: Purestar Productions MTV Workshop
description:
Sat 18th January 2014
1pm-4pm 10-14 yrs
4.30pm-7.30pm 14+ yrs

Tim Noble, international choreographer to the stars of MTV, will be holding 2 very special Commercial Jazz dance workshops at Dance HQ.
 
Prepare to be inspired!
 
If you love to dance this is a MUST ATTEND EVENT.

name: Class Card
description:
The newest, most flexible way for you to attend our great classes is with our unique Class Cards. Available in 10, 20 or 30 classes and valid for 2 months, another great way to pay for your classes.

10 classes = £55 (£5.50 per class)
20 classes = £105 (£5.25 per class)
30 classes = £150 (£5.00 per class)

Cards are activated upon your first class and are valid for 2 calendar months. 
Cards are valid for weekly, adult classes only.
Cards MUST be produced & stamped by Dance HQ when attending classes or you will be charged the full drop in rate.
Cards are non-transferable and non-refundable.

name: Blaze Dance Academy Firecrackers
description:
Saturday 1030-1100
Miss Ruth
Pre-3s with a Parent

Get moving with props, stories and fun games designed to take you and your child on an imaginative and creative journey around the world and beyond. You’re never too young to start dancing!

Suitable for children under 3 with a parent. 

PLEASE WRITE YOUR CHILD'S NAME IN THE COMMENTS BOX WHEN BOOKING, THANKS.

name: Blaze Dance Academy Starlite
description:
Saturday 1000-1030
Miss Susan
3-5 years

A fun, creative class to introduce pre-school children to the basics of ballet & tap dance.

Suitable for children aged 3-5 years

PLEASE WRITE YOUR CHILD'S NAME IN THE COMMENTS BOX WHEN BOOKING, THANKS.

name: Blaze Dance Academy Junior 1 Classes
description:
Various Times
Miss Susan & Miss Ali
5-7 years

Ballet - Saturday 1030-1100
Arguably the style from which all others develop, ballet will develop grace, poise, strength and stamina as well as providing a great base knowledge of dance.

Tap - Saturday 1100-1130
Starting with simple beats and eventually building up to complex rhythms, this class develops musicality and co-ordination whilst developing strong ankles and joints.

Modern Dance - Saturday 1130-1200
A great fun dance style, often used in musical theatre. Includes isolations, high kicks, turns and jumps to create a physically demanding yet enjoyable dance class.

Contemporary - Saturday 1200-1230
Contemporary requires fluid movements, control and creativity. It is the style of dance taught in most dance college and university courses so is essential for those hoping for a career in dance.

Musical Theatre - Monday 1830-1930
Become a 'triple threat' by adding drama and singing lessons to your weekly dance classes. This class will work towards examinations with the Trinity College London syllabus.

PLEASE WRITE YOUR CHILD'S NAME IN THE COMMENTS BOX WHEN BOOKING, THANKS.

name: Blaze Dance Academy Junior 2 Classes
description:
Various Times
Miss Susan & Miss Ali
8+ years

Tap - Thursday 1800-1830
Starting with simple beats and eventually building up to complex rhythms, this class develops musicality and co-ordination whilst developing strong ankles and joints.

Ballet - Thursday 1830-1900
Arguably the style from which all others develop, ballet will develop grace, poise, strength and stamina as well as providing a great base knowledge of dance.

Modern Dance - Thursday 1900-1930
A great fun dance style, often used in musical theatre. Includes isolations, high kicks, turns and jumps to create a physically demanding yet enjoyable dance class.

Street Dance - Thursday 1930-2000
Street Dance covers most urban dance styles including hip hop and breakdance. It is high energy and high impact and demands lots of attitude.

Contemporary - Thursday 2000-2030
Contemporary requires fluid movements, control and creativity. It is the style of dance taught in most dance college and university courses so is essential for those hoping for a career in dance.

Musical Theatre - Monday 1830-1930 
Become a 'triple threat' by adding drama and singing lessons to your weekly dance classes. This class will work towards examinations with the Trinity College London syllabus.

PLEASE WRITE YOUR CHILD'S NAME IN THE COMMENTS BOX WHEN BOOKING, THANKS.

name: Adult Graded Ballet
description:
Wednesdays 1930-2100
Robert Doherty
1930-2015 Grade 5 BATD
2015-2100 Grade 3 BATD

Finally a ballet class for adults that enables you to progress through graded exams without having to join a children's class.

This class will follow the BATD ballet syllabus and is divided into two separated graded groups - Grade 5 will work from 1930-2015 and Grade 3 will work from 2015-2100.

This course requires a commitment to attend from all participants and must be booked in advance.  Please ensure you book the correct grade and attend the specified class time for your level.  If you are unsure or need to work towards a different grade, please email dance@dancehq.co.uk for advice.

Examination fees are not included.

name: Associate Ballet
description:
Sundays 1pm-3pm
Sarah Peachey
Level 3

Following many requests we are delighted to be able to offer the BATD Associate Ballet syllabus. This class is suitable for anyone wishing to start a career in teaching dance or those looking to enhance their current qualifications.

Course content involves Barre work, Centre work, Pointe exercises at the Barre and in the Centre, a 2 min solo choreographed by the candidate and a verbal test of ballet theory and teaching methods.  Every candidate will be issued with a course handbook and will be guided through every aspect of the syllabus.

This course requires a commitment to attend from all participants and must be booked in advance. It is expected to last 20 weeks and payments are due monthly.

Examination fees are not included.

Please email dance@dancehq.co.uk prior to booking to verify you have the correct qualifications to begin this course.

name: Adult Graded Tap
description:
Wednesdays 1930-2030
Susan Elena
Grade 4 & Elementary BATD

Finally a tap class for adults that enables you to progress through graded exams without having to join a children's class.

This class will follow the BATD tap syllabus and cover a maximum of 2 grades appropriate for the group - this will be assessed by the tutor once the group is established.

This course requires a commitment to attend from all participants and must be booked in advance.  If you are unsure of which grade is right for you or need to work towards a different grade, please email dance@dancehq.co.uk for advice.

Examination fees are not included.

name: Associate Tap
description:
Saturday 1pm-2pm
Susan Elena
Level 3

Following many requests we are delighted to be able to offer the BATD Associate Tap syllabus. This class is suitable for anyone wishing to start a career in teaching dance or those looking to enhance their current qualifications.

Course content involves amalgamations at the Barre and in the Centre, plus dances of different time signatures and tempos, including one choreographed by the candidate plus a verbal test of Tap theory and teaching methods. Every candidate will be issued with a course handbook and will be guided through every aspect of the syllabus.

This course requires a commitment to attend from all participants and must be booked in advance. It is expected to last 20 weeks and payments are due monthly.

Examination fees are not included.

Please email dance@dancehq.co.uk prior to booking to verify you have the correct qualifications to begin this course.

name: Beginners Ballet
description:
Tuesdays 1830-1930
Stacey Jardine
Level 1

If you've never done ballet before but always wanted to try it, this is the class for you. You'll be taken through all the basics and taught simple sequences aimed at improving your technique.

Suitable for complete beginners and those returning to ballet.

name: Intermediate Ballet
description:
Wednesdays 1830-1930
Robert Doherty
Level 2

This is an intermediate suitable for people with some experience in ballet. Participants will be able to develop knowledge and skills in class with an aim to improve strength, technique, flexibility and co-ordination all under the guidance of a professional dancer and teacher.

A knowledge of the basics of ballet is essential for this class.

name: Advanced Ballet
description:
Sundays 1500-1600 
Sarah Peachey
Level 3

Challenge yourself to a professional level Ballet class every Sunday. This is an Advanced class suitable for those who have studied dance at college or university level or those who have trained in Ballet for several years and are looking for something to push them further.

Strong knowledge of ballet is essential for this class.

Starts Sunday 13th October

name: Barre & Stretch
description:
Monday 1830-1930
Open Level

Want a dancer’s body with long, lean limbs and a strong core?  This is the class for you.  Barre work will improve muscle tone and strength whilst the floor stretches make sure those footballers legs stay on the footballers.  Walk out feeling a million dollars and inches taller.

name: Blaze
description:
Tuesdays 1930-2030
Susan Elena
Performance Group

Blaze dancers have performed in numerous theatres and venues since they formed in 2004. Now, with a new base at Dance HQ, they plan to develop their technique further and incorporate a wider range of dance styles.

Blaze is a performance group so a commitment to attend weekly classes is required.

We are looking for more dancers to join us for our next performance so why not get in touch and give it a go.

name: Cheerleading
description:
Mondays 2030-2130
Daryl Robertson
Open Level

2, 4, 6, 8 This brand new class is really great!
3, 5, 7, 9 Don't be shy and get in line!

Ok, maybe our cheers need some work but this fantastic new class will work on every aspect of Cheerleading, including cheers that are much better than ours. Get fit the fun way with high kicks, high Vs, pom poms and formations.

Pom poms are not essential but they're so much fun! Book now and choose to add pom poms to your order.

options.name: 2x Plastic Poms with Baton Handle Red
2x Plastic Poms with Baton Handle White
2x Plastic Poms with Baton Handle Red/White

name: Contemporary Choreography
description:
Tuesday 1930-2030 
Stacey Jardine 
Open Level

Each month, this class will create a new piece of choreography, giving participants the chance to create, learn and have an input in the choreographic process of creating a small piece of work.

Different themes and stimuli will be the starting point for a new short dance piece every block, which could take inspiration from anything such as music, life or a picture. The	class	explores	the qualities	of	released and off-balance dancing while daring students to find disparate	qualities of stillness	and explosion.	Students are encouraged to develop an individual style driven by their	internal life	and the motion of their bodies.

Over the course of the block we will work on new sections of material and on the final week, using Merce Cunningham's chance technique, we will accumulate and structure a diverse dance piece.

This class is suitable for beginners to contemporary dance.

name: Fierce Fit
description:
Tuesdays 1830-1930
Susan Elena
Open Level

We hate the gym just as much as everyone else but that doesn't mean we can't enjoy working out.

Blast away those cobwebs with our brand new Fierce Fit class.  The perfect combination of cardio and toning set to the hottest soundtrack will whittle away the inches and leave you feeling fantastic.

name: Fierce Heels
description:
Mondays 1930-2030
Natalie Murray
Open Level

Unleash your inner Diva in our fabulous new High-Heel Commercial Class!

Channel Sasha Fierce and bring your hottest heels to this dance class with a difference at Dance HQ.  Work those hair flicks (and your core muscles) and strut out the door with legs to die for!

We don’t care if you’re a boy or a girl as long as you’ve got the attitude for FIERCE HEELS.

name: Flamenco
description:
Thursdays 1830-1930
Paula Gonzalez
Open Level

Feel that Spanish fire in your belly with our fantastic Flamenco class. Suitable for all levels, this class will teach you everything you need to know about Palmas (clapping rhythms), Zapateado (footwork), Braceo (arm lines) and Diagonals (combinations).

Our Spanish-born tutor will ensure you get the real, authentic Flamenco experience.

Uno, dos, tres... Olé

name: Floor Barre
description:
Thursdays 1930-2030
Lucy Weir
Open Level

Zena Rommett Floor Barre Technique ® is a gentle and effective method that lengthens and strengthens muscle, releases tension from the neck and joints and promotes correct alignment. Based on the principles of classical ballet, Floor Barre ® is a system designed to work for bodies of all ages, office workers, athletes, dancers and the general public. There are no ballet barres in sight – the whole class takes place on the floor, and no dance experience is required at all.

Lucy is one of a handful of certified Floor Barre ® instructors in the UK, and she is the only certified teacher of the technique in Scotland.

name: Pilates
description:
Saturday 1130-1230
Silvia Catani
Open Level

Pilates may seem to be a gentle and easy form of exercise; however its combination of strengthening and mobility moves can create a very intense and highly beneficial workout. High fitness levels or great suppleness are not a necessary pre-requisite for Pilates. In fact, Pilates enhances both of these conditions, whilst strengthening the core muscles around the spine, pelvic and shoulder girdles. Pilates also develops breathing control, co-ordination and stability of the body, changing muscle lengths, relaxing and re-balancing the body.

No dance experience necessary.

*Starts 25th January

name: Pointe
description:
Mondays 1930-2030
Constance Devernay
Level 2

Pointe work takes skill & strength but most of all it takes blood, sweat & tears!  This class will help you strengthen your feet and ankles specifically for pointe work as well as improving your general technique. 

Suitable for those new to pointe work as well as those already familiar with it.  Ballet technique is essential.

name: Salsa
description:
Tuesday 2030-2130
Sam Kendall
Open Level

All the way from the streets of Havana, Cuban Salsa is fun, energetic and exciting! Always moving in a circle, Cuban Salsa includes partner work and Rueda de Casino - a sociable aspect that involves dancing within a large circle.

There's no need to bring a partner so come along and make 2014 the year of Salsa!

name: Beginners Tap
description:
Wednesdays 2030-2130
Susan Elena
Level 1

Learn the basics of tap or give yourself a quick refresher course in shuffles, beats, taps, digs, cramp rolls and timesteps. Don't worry if all that seems like a foreign language - it's much easier than you think.

name: Intermediate Tap
description:
Wednesdays 1830-1930
Susan Elena
Level 2

Tap is a great workout for body and mind. This class aims to challenge the more experienced tap dancer with complex rhythms and combinations. You must be familiar with the basics to take this class.

name: Blaze Dance Academy Kit Bags

name: First Dance Platinum
description:
Whether you're a traditional or an alternative bride your first dance with your husband is an important one. With all eyes on you, it's essential that you feel comfortable taking to the floor and whether that's simply something more than a slow shuffle or a full on spectacle incorporating the whole bridal party you're likely to benefit from a few lessons.

Lessons can be held in the Dance HQ studio, out with our regular class timetable, or in your home at a time that suits you. Dances will be choreographed with your input, so nothing will be uncomfortable or unnatural to you, and ALL tastes can be catered for.

We also welcome Civil Partnerships and can choreograph something amazing for everyone.

The Platinum package gives you 6 private lessons with one of our choreographers. Please contact Dance HQ to arrange sessions prior to booking.
